<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Events Related to UNSC, Embargo, Sanctions </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Aziz Meets Various Envoys </H4>
<F P=102> JN1803203594 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1900 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1803203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning, Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz 
conferred with ambassadors of the nonaligned nations at the UN 
Security Council. After the session, 'Aziz told journalists he 
laid out to the envoys Iraq's position on sanctions. 
  The nonaligned membership of the coucil comprises Oman, 
Djibouti, Pakistan, Nigeria, and Rwanda. 
  The deputy prime minister had earlier received at his 
residence Permanment Representative Li Xhaoxing, the PRC 
ambassador at the Security Council. 

</TEXT>

