<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin on Peace Negotiations, Talk With 'Arafat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1903193894 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1900 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1903193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1900 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin by political </F>
correspondent Gadi Sukenik "in Jerusalem, a short while ago"-- 
recorded] 
  [Text] [Rabin] I expect the resumption of the 
negotiations with Syria, Jordan, and Lebanon as soon as April, 
after the Passover and Independence Day holidays. I very much 
hope that this time, they will be held on a much more 
businesslike basis than in the past. 
  [Sukenik] Last night you spoke to 'Arafat on the phone. 
Other than discussing the UN Security Council resolution, did 
you make any promises to him that made him push to move forward? 
  [Rabin] I made no specific offers, except for stressing that 
the Palestinians as well as ourselves should in no way grant 
awards to loathsome murderers on both sides. They should not 
give any prizes to Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] or the 
Islamic Jihad, and we will not give any awards to the supporters 
of the loathsome murderer who committed the abhorrent crime in 
the Cave of the Patriarchs. 
  [Sukenik] Is the issue of evacuating settlers from Hebron 
still off the agenda? 
  [Rabin] I made no commitment, except for the pledge to stand 
by our responsibility -- in addition to the struggle against the 
Palestinian extremist terrorism which seeks to murder Israelis 
and the peace -- to provide the Palestinians with protection 
against loathsome murderers the likes of that man, who does not 
deserve to be called a human being, who committed the murder in 
the Cave of the Patriarchs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

