<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   League Urges Speedy Implementation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2003125494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1202 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2003125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Mar (MENA)--The Arab League General 
Secretariat has urged the UN Security Council to implement 
expeditiously its resolution on the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. 
  In a statement issued today, the General Secretariat cited 
Security Council Resolution 904, which condemns the massacre, 
urges measures to guarantee the safety of Palestinian civilians 
in the occupied territories, calls for international or foreign 
presence in those areas and the confiscation of the Israeli 
settlers' weapons, and urges further efforts by the peace 
conference co-sponsors to revive the peace process. 
  The statement pointed out that the contents of the 
resolution 
are guidelines that must be built upon to attain a comprehensive 
and just peace in the Middle East, particularly as its clauses 
are similar to some parts of the Arab League Council's 
resolution of 27 February on the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. 
  The Arab League General Secretariat appealed to the Security 
Council to implement its resolution with due speed, demanding 
that the resolution not be subjected to Israeli procrastination 
and evasion designed to dilute it. 
  The statement noted that expeditious implementation of the 
resolution, being in line with existing international 
agreements, will protect the unarmed Palestinian people from 
Israeli practices. 
  The Secretariat reiterated its firm position on the Arabness 
of Jerusalem and the need to abide by UN Security Council 
Resolutions 242, 252, 338, 425, and 465. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

