<H3> <TI>   PLO's Kamal Previews Meeting of Cordon States </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903151094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1305 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1903151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Mar (MENA)--Palestinian Ambassador to 
Egypt Sa'id Kamal has announced that the foreign ministers of 
the cordon states, Syria, Lebanon, Jordan, and the PLO, might 
hold a meeting on the sidelines of the Arab League session in 
Cairo next Saturday [26 March]. 
  Kamal told MENA that the aim of the meeting is to coordinate 
positions and give the five concerned Arab parties an 
opportunity to consult over future actions. This will be 
especially useful after the issue of resuming the peace talks is 
settled in light of the UN Security Council resolution adopted 
today. The resolution condemns the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre 
and backs the protection of Palestinians in the occupied 
territories. 
  Kamal said next Saturday's meeting will also discuss the 
serious negative repercussions of the massacre on the peace 
process and likely criminal plans that Israeli settlers might be 
drawing up in response to the Security Council resolution. 

</TEXT>

