<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Positive Atmosphere' Reported at Tunis Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2103071394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 21 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2103071394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli delegation will meet with PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat in Tunis today for the second time. Our Arab 
affairs correspondent Arye Gus has learned that last night's 
meeting between the sides, which was marked by a positive 
atmosphere, dealt with security arrangements in the wake of the 
UN Security Council resolution on the Hebron massacre, as well 
as with the resumption of the negotiations between Israel and 
the PLO. The sides did not deal with the demand to remove the 
settlers from Hebron. It is also possible that the Israeli 
delegation will meet with U.S. mediator Dennis Ross in Tunis. 
The delegation is scheduled to return to Israel tonight. 

</TEXT>

