<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ross Holds Meetings With Palestinians, Israelis </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Arafat, Ross Meet </H4>
<F P=102> LD2103192594 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dennis Ross, U.S coordinator for Middle East 
Affairs, arrived in Tunis this afternoon and immediately met 
with Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat. It has been learned 
from the PLO headquarters that these talks are focussing on the 
formal resumption of the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations after 
the UN Security Council condemned, in its Resolution No. 904, 
the massacre at the Tomb of Patriarchs [in Hebron]. 
  The Palestinian president had earlier met, for the second 
time since yesterday, an Israeli delegation that is carrying 
proposals on security measures to be taken by Israel to ensure 
the protection of the Palestinians in the occupied territories. 
The Israelis have said that they would implement these measures 
only after a date for the resumption of talks on autonomy in 
Gaza and Jericho is announced. 
  In an interview with the U.S. newspaper NEW YORK TIMES, 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat had said that it was very 
difficult to resume talks with Israel under the pressure of 
aggressive practices [as heard] and that talks held under such 
conditions would not last very long. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

