<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ross Holds Meetings With Palestinians, Israelis </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Abd-Rabbuh: No `Tangible Results' </H4>
<F P=102> NC2103185494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1820 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2103185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 21 Mar (MENA)--Dennis Ross, U.S. coordinator 
on the peace process in the Middle East, described his talks 
with Palestinian leader Yasir 'Arafat today as "good and 
useful." In a statement following his meeting with 'Arafat, 
which lasted about two hours this afternoon, Ross said that he 
will continue the talks with 'Arafat and his aides this evening. 
  Meanwhile, PLO Executive Committee member Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh 
said that today's talks with Ross did not yield tangible 
results. 'Abd-Rabbuh, who took part in the talks, said that the 
issues that were discussed with Ross included providing 
international protection for the Palestinian people in the 
occupied territories, the form of the international presence 
approved by the Security Council in these territories, and the 
status of the Israeli settlements. 

</TEXT>

