<H3> <TI>   Ross Holds Meetings With Palestinians, Israelis </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ross Briefs Israeli Delegation </H4>
<F P=102> NC2103200994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1930 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2103200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 21 Mar (MENA)--Dennis Ross, U.S. coordinator 
on the peace process in the Middle East, this evening met with 
the Israeli delegation currently visiting Tunis to discuss ways 
of resuming the negotiations between the PLO and Israel and 
implement the Declaration of Principles agreement. Ross briefed 
the Israeli delegation on the outcome of his talks with 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat today on the possibility of 
resuming the talks as quickly as possible. The Israeli 
delegation briefed Ross on the results of its meeting with the 
Palestinian party yesterday evening, the Palestinian stance on 
the Israeli proposals to resume these negotiations, and the 
conditions the PLO is making for a return to the negotiating 
table. 
  The Israeli delegation, which includes Uri Savir, foreign 
ministry director general, and General Amnon Shahaq, deputy 
chief of staff and head of the Israeli delegation to the Taba 
talks, arrived in Tunis yesterday. 

</TEXT>

