<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leader, Colleagues Referred to Criminal Court </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903190994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1805 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1903190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Mar (MENA)-- Prosecutor General Counselor 
Raja' al-'Arabi today decided to refer Labor Party Leader 
Engineer Ibrahim Shukri; Majdi Ahmad Husayn, chief editor of the 
party's mouthpiece AL-SHA'B; and Muhammad Zaghlul and 
'Abd-al-Rahman 'Abbas, journalists working in the paper, to the 
criminal court on the charge of slandering and libeling People's 
Assembly Deputy Thurayya Labanah. 
  The prosecution statement said that in handling the issue of 
the Madinat Nasr billionaire, the defendants published in issues 
No. 809 and 810 of the paper stories in which they accused Mrs. 
Labanah of helping some law breakers in return for obtaining 
apartments. 

</TEXT>

