<H3> <TI>   Security Sweeps Launched To Arrest Terrorists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2203062594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2320 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2203062594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Mar (MENA)--Intensive security campaigns 
have been launched in various parts of Cairo to arrest fugitive 
terrorists and outlaws. Regular units from the police force, 
central security, the state security intelligence, Cairo 
intelligence department, public security, and the traffic 
department took part in these campaigns which began early this 
morning. The forces that took part in these campaigns are 
continuing their tasks in the various slum areas in 'Ayn Shams, 
al-Basatin, certain areas in central Cairo, and the suburbs. 
These campaigns are scheduled to extend to the areas east, 
west, north, and south of Cairo and will continue for several 
days. 

