<H3> <TI>   Ghawshah Comments on Executive Committee Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2103172594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1635 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2103172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 21 Mar (MENA)--Samir Ghawshah, member of the 
PLO Executive Committee, has told a MENA correspondent in 
Tunisia that the PLO cannot agree to resume negotiations with 
Israel on the implementation of the Declaration of Principles 
until practical measures are taken to provide international 
protection to the Palestinian people living in the occupied 
territories and until the issue of settlements is satisfactorily 
addressed. 
  Ghawshah pointed out that the PLO Executive Committee met 
under Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat last night. The 
committee discussed the practical measures needed to implement 
UN Security Council 904 on the massacre at al-Ibrahimi Mosque. 
The resolution, Ghawshah noted, calls for international 
protection for the Palestinian people. 
  Ghawshah added that the committee also reviewed the outcome 
of 'Arafat's meeting yesterday with an Israeli delegation under 
Amnon Shahaq. The Israeli delegation brought no new proposals 
concerning the practical measures needed to implement the UN 
Security Council resolution, despite the fact that Israeli Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin told 'Arafat in a telephone conversation 
two days ago that the delegation would convey such proposals. 

</TEXT>

