<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   About `1000 Armed Men' Reportedly Join Government Forces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103182694 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Pashto </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As many as 1000 armed men joined forces of the 
Islamic army in Dara-e Ashraf in Pol-e Khomri, Baghlan Province. 
Quoting security sources of the country, military correspondent 
of BIA [BAKHTAR INFORMATION AGENCY] reported that forces of the 
Islamic army and mojahedin of Baghlan Province captured Dar-e 
Ashraf and security posts around Karkar coal mine in their 
recent operations, and in the course of [word indistinct] 
operation cleared a number of areas of Golboddin-Dostom militia. 
In the course of the operation 1000 armed men joined the ranks 
of the Islamic army. In recent days mojahedin of the northern 
provinces of the country and the armed forces have cleared many 
areas one after another, and have freed the afflicted people of 
those areas from the oppression of Golboddin and Dostum. After 
the conquest of the North Salang, Khinjan, Doshi, and Konduz 
Province, the advance of the Islamic army and mojahedin continue 
toward Pol-e Khomri and Mazar-e Sharif. 
  According to a report of the security sources, the advance 
towards Pol-e Khomri and Dara-e Kayan continues. And losing 
their combat morale, militia leave battle fronts and escape. 
Similarly the series of surrenders to the islamic and mojahedin 
of the militia goes on. The resistance of the militia crumbles 
in Pol-e Khomri after the fall of Dara-e Ashraf and the security 
posts in its periphery;, their despair increases. The source 
said five security posts had been captured in the surrounding 
area of Karkar coal mine, and 60 militia were captured, four 
militia were killed, and five others were injured. Similarly 30 
Kalashnikovs, three rocket launchers, one 82-mm artillery piece, 
three wireless sets, and one BM-1 rocket launcher set have been 
captured. According to another report the stratigically 
important security post of Sholana in the northeast of Division 
83 has been captured. As a result 35 militia have been taken 
prisoner, (?three) Kalashnikovs, three rocket launchers, two 
ZK-1 machine guns, and one R109 wireless set have been captured. 
Operations against militia continue in those areas. 

</TEXT>

