<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pakistan Decision To Close Bombay Mission, `Regretted' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2103130294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2103130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India today regretted Pakistan's decision to close 
its consulate office in Bombay. Responding to a question at the 
daily briefing in New Delhi today, the spokesman of the External 
Affairs Ministry said Islamabad's action falls into the 
continuing and regrettable pattern of taking negative actions 
which are not conducive to good neighborly relations. He 
pointed out that India has always tried to assist in creating a 
climate in which the Pakistani Consulate can perform its 
functions. Regarding accommodation, the spokesman said Pakistan 
was not interested in certain locations offered by the 
Maharashtra Government as was clarified by the chief minister 
himself. He said Pakistanis themselves know the accommodation 
problem in metropolitan cities and pointed out that India is 
paying markets rates for its properties in Islamabad and Karachi. 

</TEXT>

