<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto -- Kashmir Issue Threatens Regional Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2203083694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in 
English 0800 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2203083694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, has said 
Pakistan cannot ignore its defense requirements and will 
continue to strengthen its defense forces within its limited 
resources. Addressing the Punjab regiment darbar [meeting] in 
Mardan today, she said Pakistan does not want confrontation with 
any country. However, the issue of Jammu and Kashmir has 
threatened the security of the region. She said Pakistan wants 
a peaceful and an early solution to the Kashmir issue. Ms. 
Benazir Bhutto stressed the need for a united strategy on 
national issues, including Jammu and Kashmir. She called on 
political parties to get together and draw up a joint strategy 
on the issue. The prime minister said the strength of the 
nation depends on the economy and therefore economic development 
of the country is top priority of her government. Referring to 
the law and order situation, she said the government is 
utilizing all its resources to eradicate social evils, including 
drug trafficking. She announced a grant of Rupees 80 lakhs for 
the Punjab regiment. 

</TEXT>

