<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Office Closes Bombay Mission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2003112194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1100 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2003112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has decided to close down its Consulate 
General in Bombay with immediate effect. 
  The Indian High Commissioner in Islamabad was called to the 
Foreign Office today and informed of Pakistan's decision. A 
spokesman of the Foreign Office said that this decision was 
taken because the Consulate General found it impossible to 
function effectively due to noncooperative and negative attitude 
of Indian authorities. The spokesman recalled that Indian 
Government had gone back on its commitment to leave the Jinnah 
House for use of the Consulate General in Bombay. The Indian 
authorities had even refused to (?permit) the acquisition of the 
principal premises for the Consulate General. The Maharashtra 
Government had in fact acted in a manner that made it extremely 
difficult for the Consulate General to carry out its assigned 
functions. 

</TEXT>

