<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arabs, Muslims Urged To Pressure U.S. on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2203093894 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 22 Mar 94 pp 1, 19 </F>
<F P=103> JN2203093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "For Arab-Muslim Complexion of Jerusalem"] </F>
  [Text] The international community, as well as Arabs and 
Muslims, ought to lend a hand to Jordan's broad-based drive for 
U.S. recognition that Jerusalem is part of the occupied Arab 
territories. 
  To quote His Majesty King Husayn, it is vital that 
Washington 
be bound by previously U.S.-endorsed UN resolutions granting the 
Arab identity of [east] Jerusalem. 
  We will not beat around the bush. With all honesty we will 
tell all Arab and Muslim nations they have to back the Jordanian 
moves and join His Majesty King Husayn's drive to uphold the 
Arab-Islamic complexion and sanctity of Jerusalem. The absence 
of Arab solidarity and a less-than-firm Islamic position has 
tempted Israel to pursue its expansionist ambitions in the 
occupied Arab territories, most of all in Jerusalem. It has 
also prompted the United States to backtrack on previous 
positions and so abstain on the Jerusalem part of UN Security 
Council Resolution 904. 
  Should this kind of Arab and Islamic position persist, the 
Arab-Islamic complexion of Jerusalem will be commandeered in 
broad daylight with U.S., and maybe international, support. 
  Arab and Muslim leaders cannot afford to remain mere 
spectators as the Arab-Islamic complexion of Jerusalem, the 
al-Aqsa Mosque, and the Dome of the Rock is hijacked. It is the 
duty of every Arab and Muslim to strive to maintain the identity 
of this holy city. Under no circumstances should we remain 
passive toward the plot to confiscate Jerusalem's identity and 
Judaize it and its Islamic shrines. 
  Hence our argument that all Arab and Muslim leaders must 
heed 
His Majesty King Husayn's call and join forces with him to 
preempt the confiscation of Jerusalem's identity and bring 
sufficient pressure to bear in the interest of a renewed 
commitment by the U.S. Administration to the UN Security Council 
resolutions according to which Jerusalem is occupied territory 
not subject to annexation by Israel under any circumstances. 
  If the U.S. Administration really cares about a viable peace 
process, it will have to rethink its positions and obligate 
itself to UN resolutions and the terms of reference of the 
Madrid conference that the United States itself initiated. 
Otherwise, the peace process is doomed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

