<H3> <TI>   King Visits Wounded From Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2003203494 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2003203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn this evening visited the 
wounded victims from the Holy Ibrahimi Mosque's massacre, who 
are receiving medical treatment at the al-Husayn Medical Center 
in Amman and reassured himself about their condition and the 
treatment they receive from their brothers in this esteemed 
medical establishment. 
  The wounded patients expressed thanks and appreciation to 
His 
Majesty King Husayn for his generous Hashemite initiative toward 
the victims of the ugly massacre, committed in the holy Ibrahimi 
Mosque during the blessed month of Ramadan, and Jordan's 
honorable pan-Arab position, under the leadership of his majesty 
in support of their brothers the sons of the Palestinian people 
and the holy shrines in all circumstances. 
  His Majesty King Husayn had ordered the formation of a 
higher 
committee to raise donations for the massacre's victims. His 
majesty donated a sum of 100,000 dinars for the victims, and 
ordered that everything possible be provided to assist the 
wounded in Jordanian hospitals. 
  King Husayn was accompanied by His Highness Prince Hamzah 
Bin-al-Husayn, and al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, Royal Hashemite 
Court chief. 

</TEXT>

