<F P=102>  TA2103095894 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 21 Mar 94 pp 
1, 8 </F>

<F P=103> TA2103095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Pe'erli Shahar, U.S. correspondent Natan Gutman, </F>
Pinhas 'Inbari, and news agencies] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The establishment of the 
Palestinian police force in Gaza and Jericho will be given top 
priority in the resuming talks with the PLO and in the 
preliminary contacts. Israeli sources noted that Israel has 
acceded to the PLO demand to actually make it a paramilitary 
force, alongside the "blues." 
  In recent days, the PLO leadership has given its permission 
to reinstate some of the policemen who served under Israel and 
who quit their jobs during the intifadah. PLO official Ziyad 
'Arif met last Saturday in Khan Yunus with those policemen. He 
told them to be ready to return to service on 15 April and 
handed them their first salary. 
  The Israeli sources pointed out that this police force will 
begin operating in the autonomy areas before the Palestine 
Liberation Army deploys its troops and will work in coordination 
with the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] authorities until the 
Israeli withdrawal. 

</TEXT>

