<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Terrorist,' Israeli Hurt in Territories Incidents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2003115594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 20 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2003115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A terrorist has been seriously wounded by Border 
Police gunfire in the Gaza Strip. Our correspondent Moti Amir 
reports that shots were fired at a Border Police patrol from a 
passing car. The policemen were unharmed and returned the fire. 
The terrorists fled in a car. Later, one of them arrived with 
serious wounds at a Gaza hospital and was arrested. 
  An Israeli citizen sustained serious head injuries when 
stones were hurled at him in central Ramallah. He fled to an 
adjacent cafe where Arab patrons who tried to protect him were 
also attacked. The man barely managed to escape to a police 
station in Ramallah. His car was torched. 

</TEXT>

