<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Blind Arab Dies After Being Shot by IDF, 16 Wounded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2103171894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1600 GMT 21 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2103171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At least 16 Palestinians have been wounded during 
disturbances today in the territories, nine in Qalqilyah, five 
in the Gaza Strip, and two in Bethlehem. In Hebron, a protest 
rally was staged against the curfew on the town and the massacre 
at the Cave of the Patriarchs. Although there were some clashes 
in the morning, later in the day the Israeli security forces 
refrained from intervening. 
  A 28-year-old blind Palestinian from Gaza has died in 
hospital from wounds after being shot, reportedly in error, by 
the Border Police. The man, Ahmad Ali, who came from the 
al-Shaja'iyah neighborhood, apparently got caught up in an 
exchange of fire when gunmen attacked the Border Police. 

</TEXT>

