<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amir of Bahrain Arrives in Damascus on Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Amir Meets al-Asad, Makes Statements </H4>
<F P=102> JN2003211394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1215 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2003211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] His Highness Shaykh 'Isa Bin-Salman Al Khalifah, 
the amir of Bahrain, arrived in Damascus at 1130 today on a 
visit to the Syrian Arab Republic. President Hafiz al-Asad led 
those who received him at Damascus International Airport. Also 
present at the airplane ramp were Vice Presidents 'Abd-al-Halim 
Khaddam and Dr. Muhammad Zuhayr Mashariqah, Prime Minister 
Mahmud al-Zu'bi, Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar', and Bahrain's 
Ambassador in Damascus Muhammad Hamad al-Muhaymid. [passage 
omitted] 
  After a brief rest at the airport's VIP lounge, President 
Hafiz al-Asad and his important guest left in an official 
motorcade for Tishrin Palace, where his highness will reside. 
His Highness Shaykh 'Isa is accompanied by an official 
delegation, including Foreign Minister Shaykh Muhammad 
Bin-Mubarak, Interior Minister Shaykh Muhammad Bin-Khalifah Al 
Khalifah, Transportation Minister Shaykh 'Ali Bin-Khalifah Al 
Khalifah, Information Minister Tariq 'Abd-al-Rahman al-Mu'ayyad, 
Finance and National Economy Minister Ibrahim 'Abd-al-Karim 
Muhammad, Minister of Trade and Agriculture Habib Ahmad Qasim, 
and Amiri Court Chief Yusuf Rahmah al-Dusari. 
  President Hafiz al-Asad and His Highness Shaykh 'Isa 
Bin-Salman Al Khalifah held a meeting in Tishrin Palace attended 
by the Bahraini delegation accompanying the amir. On the Syrian 
side, the meeting was attended by Vice Presidents 'Abd-al-Halim 
Khaddam and Muhammad Zuhayr Mashariqah, Prime Minister Mahmud 
al-Zu'bi, Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar', Interior Minister Dr. 
Muhammad Harbah, Information Minister Dr. Muhammad Salman, 
Economy and Foreign Trade Minister Dr. Muhammad al-'Imadi, 
Presidential Affairs Minister Wahib Fadil, Agriculture Minister 
As'ad Mustafa, and Transportation Minister Dr. Radwan Martini. 
  In a statement to the media, Shaykh 'Isa Bin-Salman Al 
Khalifah said: It is my pleasure to be on this brotherly visit 
to the sisterly Syrian Arab Republic--the cradle of Arab 
civilization, the launching pad for pan-Arab awakening, and the 
rallying point for the Arabs--in order to meet with brother 
President Hafiz al-Asad whom we hold in deep respect and 
fondness for what his excellency enjoys in terms of pan-Arab 
devotion and a farsighted vision of current Arab and 
international developments. This is in addition to his 
honorable and firm principled stands on pan-Arab issues and 
toward all Arab brothers in the big Arab Homeland. 
  It is also my pleasure to express during this visit the deep 
feelings of love and solidarity the government and people of 
Bahrain have toward the fraternal Syrian people and their 
national government. Our fraternal countries met, each from 
their vital position in the Arab world, on the road to national 
commitment and adherence to the joint interests of our Arab 
nation in terms of its awakening and building. Syria has played 
a distinguished Arab role since the beginning of the process by 
spreading enlightened Arab awareness, entrenching the values of 
Arab civilization and culture, standing in solidarity with our 
fraternal Arab brothers at various stages and against all 
challenges. 
  Fraternal Syria's stand during the October 1973 war, 
championing the Arab right to Palestine and the Arab territories 
had a great impact in creating an effective Arab consensus. We 
are now in real need for solidarity under the critical 
circumstances we are facing to confront the rapid challenges and 
developments in the region and around the world. We now 
reaffirm our full support for the comprehensive peace process 
based on pan-Arab constants and principles to which we, along 
with sisterly Syria and fraternal Arabs, adhere. We must 
reaffirm that in order to achieve stability and development for 
the people of the entire region, the peace process should be 
based on the principle of comprehensive and just peace. 
  Peace cannot pervail without restoring the territories. Land 
should be exchanged for peace. Based on this basic principle, 
we reaffirm that Bahrain supports Syria's demand for a full 
Israeli withdrawal from its occupied territories and its 
legitimate right to the full return of the occupied Syrian Golan 
to Syrian sovereignty without encroaching on its international 
borders under any claim whatsoever. 
  On another pan-Arab level, we must praise Syria's just stand 
on the issue of liberating Kuwait and returning it to its 
owners. In continuation of this positive stand, Syria's 
coordination with its sisterly states in the Gulf Cooperation 
Council and with Egypt within the framework of the Damascus 
declaration is the best formula to support the march of Arab 
cooperation. 
  In conclusion, we look forward to more steps toward 
coordination and cooperation between our two fraternal countries 
during this renewed brotherly meeting with brother President 
Hafiz al-Asad and his countrymen as a reinforcement of our 
distinguished and constructive brotherly relations. We believe 
that these relations are a positive and advanced model in the 
march of joint Arab action. An Arab greeting from Bahrain to the 
leadership and people of Syria, the stronghold of Arabism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

