<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amir of Bahrain Arrives in Damascus on Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Asad, Amir Exchange Awards </H4>
<F P=102> JN2003212994 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network in 
Arabic 1830 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2003212994 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad and His Highness Shaykh 'Isa 
Bin-Salman Al Khalifah, the amir of Bahrain, this evening held a 
meeting at the People's Palace. The meeting was attended by 
Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' and Bahraini Foreign Minister 
Muhammad Bin-Mubarak Al Khalifah. 
  His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad awarded His Highness 
'Isa Bin-Salman Al Khalifah, the amir of Bahrain, The National 
Umayyah Medal--Sash of the First Order. Shaykh 'Isa also 
awarded the president the Gulf Pendant--the highest honor in 
Bahrain. The president and His Highness Shaykh 'Isa exchanged 
words on this occasion. The president expressed his happiness 
to award his highness the amir the National Umayyah Medal which 
symbolizes the Arab nation's glory and illustrious history, as 
well as the pan-Arab ties among all the sons of the Arab nation. 
His Highness Shaykh 'Isa expressed his thanks for the 
hospitality and generous reception which he and the accompanying 
delegation received in Syria. He said: We feel that we are in 
our country. We consider Syria and Bahrain as one country. We 
are also proud of you as a president and a leader and hope that 
Syria will triumph over its enemies. 
  The exchange of medals ceremony was attended by the official 
Bahraini delegation accompanying his highness the amir of 
Bahrain. On the Syrian side, the ceremony was attended by Vice 
Presidents 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam and Dr. Muhammad Zuhayr 
Mashariqah, Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi, and ministers Faruq 
al-Shar', Dr. Muhammad Harbah, Dr. Muhammad Salman, Dr. Muhammad 
al-'Imadi, Wahib Fadil, As'ad Mustafa, and Radwan Martini. 
  President Hafiz al-Asad this evening held a dinner banquet 
in 
honor of Syria's guest His Highness Shaykh 'Isa Bin-Salman Al 
Khalifah, the amir of Bahrain. Also attending the banquet were 
the delegation accompanying his highness [the amir], Vice 
Presidents 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam and Dr. Muhammad Zuhayr 
Mashariqah, Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi, the deputy prime 
ministers, the ministers, secretary of the Presidential Office, 
Damascus governor, Damascus rural area governor, assistant 
ministers, Foreign Ministry departments heads, and heads of 
media organs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

