<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Rabin Reportedly To Sign `Final Measures' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2003145294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1425 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2003145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Mar (MENA)--A responsible Egyptian source 
has stated that Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli 
Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin are expected to sign the final 
measures for the implementation of the Palestinian-Israeli 
Declaration of Principles in the coming few weeks in Cairo. The 
same source noted that early empowerment may also apply to the 
Hebron area, in addition to Gaza and Jericho, adding that a 
Palestinian police force will be permitted in Hebron and a 
Palestinian mayor will be appointed there. 
  The same source stressed that the recent outlawing of the 
Kakh and Kahana terrorist movements in Israel was a considerable 
gain by the Palestinian negotiators, noting that president 
'Arafat played all his cards with great skill during the 
negotiations that followed the recent massacre at the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron. 

</TEXT>

