<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Constitutional Union Issues Statement on New Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2103142694 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 20 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2103142694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Libyan Constitutional Union"] </F>
  [Excerpt] London, AL-HAYAH -- AL-HAYAH has received a 
statement from Shaykh Muhammad Bin-Ghalbun, leader of the Libyan 
Constitutional Union, commenting on recent developments in the 
Libyan opposition, dwelling specifically on the breaking away of 
a group from the National Front for the Salvation of Libya (the 
main opposition faction) and the subsequent establishment of the 
Libyan Movement for Change and Reform. Bin-Ghalbun said: 
"Since that group broke away there have been voices calling for 
prudence and trying to dissuade this group from its plan under 
the pretext of unity, claiming that splits weaken the unity of 
ranks and serve the interests of the regime only. But that is 
untrue, because the split is prompted by the care for national 
interests and aimed at correcting and strengthening the moderate 
national line." He expressed his hope that "the new 
organization will become one of the active and strong Libyan 
organizations. I know some of the men responsible for its 
establishment, management, and guidance. They are capable of 
shouldering the responsibility and are experienced and 
knowledgeable and their national commitment and sincerity are 
above all suspicion." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

