<F P=102>  NC2003071794 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 0530 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2003071794 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Investigations into the recent wave of bombings 
remain the focus of attention, particularly after emerging clues 
that point clearly to the party that stands behind them. This 
prompted the army command to take basic measures and to deploy 
units in this party's centers that were used for planning these 
bombings. 
  Visitors of President Ilyas al-Hirawi, citing him, told our 
radio that there were four detainees in the bombing of the 
Sayyidat al-Najat church, and that two others managed to flee to 
the occupied border strip. 
  THE NATIONAL NEWS AGENCY, quoting concerned parties, said 
that the results of the investigations into the bombing will be 
made public next week at a meeting at Justice Minister Bahij 
Tabbarah's office. 

