<F P=100> INDIAN VIEWS </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Comparison of Kashmir, Afghanistan Criticized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94AS0206B Bangalore DECCAN HERALD in English 12 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94AS0206B </F>
<F P=104>  Bangalore DECCAN HERALD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Excerpt] New Delhi, Feb 11--India today firmly rejected a 
recent reference by the United States to the situation in 
Kashmir, comparing it to the situation in Afghanistan and 
asserted that such references betrayed the "lack of balance and 
proper perspective" on the part of U.S. officials which was 
tantamount to providing "encouragement to Pakistan and 
terrorists sustained by them to continue with their violent 
activities." 
  Noting that the remarks recently made in Washington by the 
U.S. Assistant Secretary of State for South Asian Affairs, Ms. 
Robin Raphel, a spokesman of the Ministry of External Affairs 
today said the comparison was grossly misplaced as the Afghan 
situation was a by-product of the Cold War whereas Jammu and 
Kashmir has been facing a massive campaign of terrorism aided 
and abetted by Pakistan. The only link between the two was that 
the weapons and mercenaries were moved from both Afghanistan and 
Pakistan to foment trouble in Kashmir, the spokesman said. 
[passage omitted] 
* 

</TEXT>

