<F P=100> INDIAN VIEWS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Says Kashmir Open to Foreign Journalists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1603101194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1603101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The minister of state for external affairs, Mr. 
R.L. Bhatia, said over 150 foreign journalists visited Jammu and 
Kashmir last year. In a written reply in the Rajya Sabha today, 
he said Pakistan has been indulging in a disinformation campaign 
alleging that members of international media cannot visit Jammu 
and Kashmir. He said the government is taking all steps to 
inform the international community that there is no restriction 
on visits of foreign journalists to the state. 

</TEXT>

