<H3> <TI>   Paper Affirms Captured Arms Plane Bound for South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2003193094 Omdurman National Unity Radio in English 1500 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2003193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman National Unity Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The editor of the African affairs at the 
London-based INDEPENDENT newspaper has affirmed that the plane 
which carries arms being captured at Cyprus was intended to the 
outlaws' movement in southern Sudan, according to what diplomats 
and political analysts state. [words indistinct] outlaws have 
been receiving arms secretly and they think that United States 
and its alliance are the source of these arms. The British 
journalist goes on to say that Washington has offered the green 
light to one of its allies in the area to provide arms to the 
outlaws' movement from the American arms stores following the 
Gulf war. He pointed out that the plane which is now in Cyprus 
is a part of the campaign to overcome the lack of arms in the 
outlaws' hands, adding that the eyewitnesses said they had seen 
a number of trucks carrying arms in the borders. 

</TEXT>

