<H3> <TI>   'Arafat's Adviser Sha'th Arrives in Cairo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2203221794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2100 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2203221794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political adviser to Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat, arrived in Cairo tonight from Tunis, 
having taken part in two days of talks between the Palestinian 
leadership; Dennis Ross, U.S. coordinator of the Middle East 
peace process; and an Israeli delegation. 
  Dr. Sha'th pointed out that he will head the Palestinian 
delegation to the meeting that will be held on 24 March by 
representatives of 21 countries to discuss assistance for the 
Palestinian police force. He added that Ross will lead the U.S. 
delegation to that meeting. 
  The Palestinian official said that the Israeli delegation is 
expected to return to that meeting with some answers to the 
Palestinian demands, particularly the one concerning security in 
Hebron, following consultations with the Israeli Government. 

</TEXT>

