<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abd-Rabbuh Cancels PLO-Israeli Meeting in Cairo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2303065694 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0600 GMT 23 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2303065694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While contacts, particularly with the PLO, are in 
full swing to resume the PLO-Israeli talks after the issuance of 
UN Security Council Resolution 904, clashes have erupted in the 
West Bank city of Hebron, where the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre 
was perpetrated. There were only small leaks about yesterday's 
confrontations due to the Israeli military censorship. REUTER 
said the Israeli Army killed a Palestinian woman, who was five 
months pregnant, while she was watching the clashes from the 
window of her house--clashes which resulted in the injury of at 
least five Palestinians. 
  In a telephone interview with our radio, Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, 
head of the PLO Information Department, confirmed the death of 
the woman and said about 30 Palestinians were wounded, and 
another three killed during the day. He added that the Israeli 
Army carried out a large-scale offensive in the city of Hebron, 
occupied the children's hospital and Queen 'Alya' Hospital, and 
fired rockets at houses on the pretext of searching for wanted 
persons. Therefore, added 'Abd-Rabbuh, today's Cairo meeting 
between the PLO and Israel will not be held. 
  This Cairo meeting was expected to be held after the failure 
of the Israeli and Palestinian sides in Tunis to agree to the 
resumption of peace talks. The meeting was scheduled to 
concentrate on the issue of protecting Palestinians in the 
occupied territories. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

