<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Tibi: 'Abd-Rabbuh Remarks `Misunderstood' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2303082894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 23 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2303082894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following consultations with the PLO leadership in 
Tunis, Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi, PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat's adviser, 
said this morning that there was no intention of suspending the 
Cairo talks. Al-Tibi asserted that the statements made by Yasir 
'Abd- Rabbuh, the head of the PLO's Information Department, were 
misunderstood. Dr. al-Tibi believes that Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh 
merely sought to highlight the obstacles events in Hebron are 
placing in the path of the autonomy talks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

