<H3> <TI>   Negotiations in Cairo Delayed for Several Hours </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2303071994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0632 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2303071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 23 Mar (MENA)--MENA has learned that the 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations on international protection for 
the Palestinians in the occupied territories, which were 
scheduled to open in Cairo at noon today, have been postponed 
until 1700 today. 
  Diplomatic sources said a change in the arrival time of the 
Israeli delegation led by Foreign Ministry Director General Uri 
Savir caused the delay. 

</TEXT>

