<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Claims Responsibility for Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2303092494 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 23 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> TA2303092494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yig'al Wilfend and ITIM] </F>
  [Excerpt] Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] has claimed 
responsibility for the attack Monday [21 March] night near the 
settlement of 'Ateret north of Ramallah. 
  A leaflet distributed yesterday in the Gaza Strip, Ramallah, 
and East Jerusalem noted that the attack near Bi'r Zayt in which 
five settlers were wounded had been perpetrated by 'Izz-al-Din 
al-Qassam troops. 
  The leaflet added that this was "the beginning of the 
implementation of the plan to expel the settlers from all the 
territories," as had been promised in a previous leaflet in 
which the settlers were given an ultimatum to leave by 15 March. 
The authors contend that this ultimatum had already caused 
several families to leave Qiryat Arba'. However, the leaflet 
noted, Hamas does not consider this sufficient "and will 
continue to strike until the last settler leaves." [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

