<F P=100> Tunisia </F>
<H3> <TI>   International Observers Satisfied With Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003185494 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In order to guarantee complete openness the presence 
of observers was ostensible at polling stations; they were 
observers from human rights organizations, as well as Tunisian 
and foreign journalists. They were all able to follow the 
voting process. The head of state had given his instructions to 
facilitate their movements in order to follow the whole voting 
process. 
  Among those who were present was the secretary general of 
the 
European Socialist Party [as heard], who made the following 
statement to the press before leaving Tunis. 
  [Begin unidentified voice recording, in French fading into 
Arab translation] I went to Sfax and Kairouan very early this 
morning to talk to voters and to those who were in charge of 
polling stations; I also talked to governors and to the Justice 
Minister. Everything went smoothly and I was very impressed 
with the high turnout and the calm that prevailed over the 
elections. 
  In Kairouan, I talked to the local opposition leaders, who 
were fighting the elections there and, as far as I am concerned, 
the opposition was satisfied with the progress of the elections. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

