<H3> <TI>   Inquiry Commission Hears Hebron Arabs' Testimony </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2203162294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1600 GMT 22 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2203162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Shamgar Commission today heard testimony from 
Palestinians who were praying in the Cave of the Patriarchs at 
the time of the massacre. Three of them claimed that they had 
heard shots fired from more than one direction, and suggested 
that Barukh Goldstein did not carry out the killings by himself. 
One of them said he heard the sound of hand grenades, as well 
as automatic gunfire. A fourth witness said soldiers prevented 
people from leaving the cave after the massacre and even raised 
their weapons, but the worshipers ignored them and went on their 
way. 

</TEXT>

