<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Committee Tries To Restore `Normality' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2203182994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2203182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Military Committee, headed by committee chairman 
Staff Colonel 'Ali Muhammad Salah, has resumed meetings and 
visits to camps and complexes in the Shabwah Governorate to 
clear the atmosphere and restore normality. 
  During these visits, the committee met with Shabwah 
Governorate officials, Shabwah axis commanders, the security 
director, representatives of parties and political 
organizations, the protests committee in the governorate, and 
residents of the city of 'Ataq. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', Staff Col. 
'Ali Muhammad Salah, chairman of the Military Committee, said 
matters had calmed down, that the situation was normal, and that 
the Military Committee found that everybody was eager to see a 
normal situation. He pointed out that the Military Committee 
will continue to carry out its duties, appealing to everyone to 
cooperate to allow it to carry its duties successfully. 

</TEXT>

