<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportedly Brokers 'Ataq Troop Pullout </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2203210794 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2203210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News at Ten" program] </F>
  [Text] Rival Yemeni parties are reported to have agreed to 
pull out their troops from the provincial capital 'Ataq in the 
southern oil-producing region of Shabwah. 
  The Jordanian-Omani military committee helping to disengage 
the two sides' armies said an agreement had been reached to 
withdraw troops from and around the city. A statement by the 
committee said all groups around the city would return to their 
bases. 
  Jordanian, Omani, and Yemeni officers, along with the 
American and French military attaches in Yemen, formed the 
committee after the country's two main political rivals signed a 
reconciliation agreement in Amman on February 20th. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

