<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Officials Asked To Leave Sanaa for Security Reasons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2203141194 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 21 Mar 94 p1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2203141194 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Reports by Naji al-Harazi in 'Ataq and Hammud Munsir in </F>
Sanaa: "The Yemeni Leadership Asks the Socialist Party and 
Opposition Leaders To Leave Sanaa"] 
  [Excerpt] Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] officials have 
confirmed that the Yemeni leadership has asked some of the YSP 
leaders still in Sanaa as well as a number of opposition leaders 
to leave Sanaa "for security reasons." 
  They added that Interior Minister Brigadier General Yahya 
al-Mutawakkil was instructed to inform Yahya al-Shami and Fish 
Resources Minister Fadl Muhsin 'Abdallah, both of whom are 
members of the YSP's Political Bureau, and Dr. 'Abd-al-Quddus 
al-Midwahi, who is one of the leaders of the Nasirite Unionist 
Organization, to leave Sanaa. They are all members of the 
Political Forces Dialogue Committee. 
  A YSP spokesman said that this "meant that people were being 
expelled from their own homeland and that the way was being 
paved for further developments later on." Sources in Sanaa 
stressed that dismissal of Engineer Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas's 
cabinet and formation of a new cabinet under the chairmanship of 
another YSP leader was being seriously considered because of the 
continuing political battle and exchange of accusations between 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and Engineer al-'Attas. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

