<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council To Meet in Sanaa 28 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2203211994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2203211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Political Forces Dialogue Committee held a 
meeting this morning under the chairmanship of brother 
'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd- al-Ghani, member of the Presidential Council. 
  At the beginning of the meeting, the minutes of the previous 
session were read and endorsed with remarks. The committee then 
reviewed the results of the subcommittees' work. The committee 
expressed satisfaction with the political leadership's response 
to the decisions to stop media campaigns by official organs, 
affirming that the media should return as it was before the 
crisis and that all campaigns by all official media organs 
should stop. The committee continued its discussion of the 
issue of reunifying the institutions in light of the proposals 
reached by the committee formed for this purpose. 
  Following consultations with the competent quarters, it has 
been agreed that the Council of Ministers will meet in the 
presence of all its members on Wednesday and Thursday [23 and 24 
March] in Aden. The Council of Ministers will then meet in 
Ta'izz and then in Sanaa. 
  Following consultations, it has been agreed that the 
Presidential Council will hold a meeting in Sanaa on Monday [28 
March] to prepare a working agenda for the meeting of all its 
members. 
  The Dialogue Committee will continue its meetings tomorrow, 
Wednesday [23 march] in the economic and trade capital Aden to 
continue discussion of topics on agenda. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

