<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Comments on King's Visit to Oman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2203154394 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 
22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2203154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, minister of </F>
state for foreign affairs, by unidentified correspondent in 
Salalah; date not given -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Correspondent] His Majesty King Husayn's visit to 
Oman is important. Would you please comment on this visit? 
  [Al-Hasan] I want to reiterate the deep and distinguished 
Jordanian-Omani relations that have been reinforced by His 
Majesty King Husayn and his brother His Majesty Sultan Qabus 
Bin-Sa'id. As you know, these relations are becoming stronger 
with time. These relations, which are fraternal in terms of 
dealing and frank in terms of coordination and consultation, 
have become an example for other countries. King Husayn's visit 
to his brother Sultan Qabus falls within this framework. These 
relations are based on the existing fraternal relations between 
the two leaders and two people. I can say these relations are 
strong, firm, and continuous. The two countries are determined 
to strengthen these relations on all levels. 
  I can also say that the high level of consultation and 
coordination will include many bilateral issues and many Arab, 
regional, and international issues. King Husayn's visit 
represents a qualitative move that will strength Jordanian-Omani 
relations. 
  [Correspondent] Your Excellency: Today, you met with the 
Omani minister of state for foreign affairs. What took place 
during the meeting? 
  [Al-Hasan] I held a fraternal meeting with my brother His 
Excellency Yusuf Bin-'Alawi, the Omani minister of state for 
foreign affairs. We reviewed our good and distinguished 
bilateral relations on the political, economic, and cultural 
levels. We discussed a number of measures to provide momentum 
to these relations, to develop them, and to activate our 
bilateral agreements. I also discussed with the minister a 
number of Arab, regional, and international issues of mutual 
interest. Thank you. 
  [Correspondent] Thank you, sir. 

</TEXT>

