<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Company Invites Businessmen to Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2203104894 Amman AL-ASWAQ in Arabic 22 Mar 94 pp 1, 14 </F>
<F P=103> JN2203104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-ASWAQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 'Azzam Jarrar: "A Normalization Attempt Via </F>
Norway"] 
  [Text] Some Jordanian food companies have received letters 
from an Israeli company called Global Information Ltd. inviting 
them to participate in some advance food industry courses, 
supervised by a British scientific research association, in the 
Hilton Hotel, Tel Aviv, next June. 
  The letter said this would be an opportunity to benefit from 
the advance courses and meet with and be introduced to 
colleagues from Israel and other countries in the region, as 
well as an opportunity to visit Tel Aviv. The letter indicated 
that the organizing company is ready to arrange hotel 
reservations, receive participants at the airport, and have 
visas issued to those needing them. 
  The letter said the organizers will be happy to arrange 
meetings with the Israeli food companies and urged participants 
not to hesitate to contact the organizers for further details. 
  The letter is signed by Avi Gordon, general manager of 
Global 
Information Ltd. It has been learned that these letters reached 
Jordan via Norway. 
  The Jordanian companies that received the letter expressed 
their surprise at and denunciation of this invitation, which 
they thought was an Israeli psychological maneuver aimed at 
breaking the Arab boycott even before concluding peace 
agreements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

