<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   SAIRI: 2 Government Battalions Join Opposition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903165594 Tehran IRNA in English 1640 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1903165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sar Dasht, Kordestan Prov, March 19, IRNA -- Two 
Iraqi battalions along with their equipment joined the 
opposition forces in Northern Iraq, a statement by the Supreme 
Assembly of the Islamic Revolution of Iraq (SAIRI) said here 
today. 
  The statement said the battalions had been stationed between 
the regions under the control of the self-declared government of 
Northern Iraq and Chamchamal region in the Karkuk Province. 
  There are six officers among the forces, possibly affiliated 
to the Iraqi First Corps, the statement said, adding that due to 
the harsh economic conditions and political isolation of Iraq, 
the number of the personnel deserting the army is increasing in 
the country. 
  According to the sources close to the SAIRI, the Iraqi 
forces 
would probably intensify their military pressures on the 
northern and southern population, in addition to increasing 
their threats against Kuwait on the coming days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

