<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baghdad Protests 8-16 Mar Airspace `Violations' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2103181294 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1130 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2103181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Iraq has informed the Arab League that U.S., 
British, and French aircraft continue to violate its airspace, 
noting that this seriously jeopardizes its security and 
sovereignty. 
  In a letter addressed to the Arab League secretary general 
yesterday, the Iraqi permanent representative to the Arab League 
said that these aircraft continued on 8-16 March to violate 
Iraqi airspace, flying from bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait. 
They carried out 321 hostile air sorties during the 
aforementioned period. 
  A list attached to the letter detailed these airspace 
violations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

